&gt;From article &lt;2425@ncsuvx.ncsu.edu&gt;, by sam@ncsuvx.ncsu.edu (Sam Moore):
&gt; To make things worse I had the changes, but operator error in my mailer
&gt; deleted that mail message. All I can remember about the person that was
&gt; so nice to send the changes to me is that his 'In real life' name was
&gt; something like "Brain dead".

That was me (just "in Neutral", not "dead", I hope).  I've mailed these
again to Sam; if anyone else is interested, the kit is a set of patches
to the BIND 4.8 distribution that will modify it to work for either 1.2
or 2.2 Ultrix.  It also will make life easier if you're trying to bring
up BSD sendmail 5.59 (i.e., MX-conversant sendmail) on an Ultrix
machine.

The kit is, I think (haven't heard otherwise :-), pretty easy to use.  You
get a clean BIND distribution, and run a shell script that patches things
up for you, then do the makes indicated in the instructions.

The instructions also include some discussion about why the changes are
necessary.  I included this because of my own difficulties in putting
together sporadic information gathered here and there; hopefully someone
else can be spared the trouble.

Paul DuBois
dubois@primate.wisc.edu	rhesus!dubois
bin@primate.wisc.edu	rhesus!bin

